SampleComment: GPS: 52.391111, -113.198056. Wind: 10 km/h SE. Waves: 0.1m. Sonde stopped reading depth properly so marked depth on cord. Saw a Muskrat swimming. Lots of bladderwort present. The whole lake is a similar depth. Microcystin ID: M200114. Probe: 60444

GPS: 52.391111, -113.198056. Wind: 10km/h S. Waves: 0.01m. Specks in the water could be Cyanobacteria. Lots of Bladderwort. Mud from the bottom smells sulphury. Did horizontal veliger tows. Microcystin ID: M200116. Probe: 41488
GPS: 52.39119, -113.19734. Wind: 6 km/h S. Waves: 0.02m. Volunteer got a new motor for their boat. Heated up to ~30 degrees as sampling progressed. Microcystin ID:M200115. Probe:47482
GPS: 52.3910, -113.19786. Wind: 5km/h S. Waves: 0. Very calm. Surrounding trees are yellow now. Campground is still operating. Used tape and weight for depth. Microcystin ID: M200113. Probe:47482

GPS: 53.49800 -112.98280. Wind: 3 km/hr W. Waves: 0. Less weed (floating) growth than last year. Water levels are up, we found a location with a depth of 2.7m. We may have drifted slightly during the Profile site reading. Microcystin ID: M200176 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 53.4962 -112.9828. Wind: 6 km/hr NW. Waves: 0.05m. Used euphotic tubing to haul water at Profile site, but discarded it and re-rinsed comp jug. Blue-green algae blooms / weeds forming scums on shorline. Open water much less effected by blue-green scums. Obtained a greater depth at profile site due to proper anchoring. Lots of terns and invertebrates on and in the lake. Microcystin ID: M200177 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 53.49806 -112.9828. Wind: 2 km/hr N. Waves: 0. More green in the Eastern portion of the Lake. Overall, less then in July. Blue-green scums previously on shoreline are gone. Weeds seem to have replaced them. Strong Odor present near shore. Microcystin ID: M200124 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8"). Total phosphorus sample re-run by lab due to disagreement of QC. New results loaded. Original COA in DIVA.
GPS: 53.49621 -112.9828. Wind: 2 km/hr SW. Waves: 0. Water was very calm. Lots of duckweed on shore. Microcystin ID: M200125 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 49.41215, -114.10356. Wind: 18 km/hr W. Waves: 0.1m. Sampled from canoe. Last half of long arm of the lake is blocked off for waterfowl nesting until July 10th every year. Did profile site accidentally further east than should've been, but was actually deepest there (swapped sites 1&2). Entire watershed is in the provincial park so lake is very clean according to Klaus. SE arm was very shallow from macrophytes. Microcystin ID: M200083. Probe: 60444. Net: Wisconsin

GPS: 49.41210, -114.10292. Wind: 13 km/hr W. Waves: 0.1m. Specks of cyanobacteria visible in water column. Long arm of lake full of weeds. Bio suggests moving profile site to in front of volunteer's house (swap sites 1 & 2 like we did last time) becasue old profile site is not very deep. Microcystin ID: M200082. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow

GPS: 49.41178, -114.10258, Wind: 8 km/hr SW. Waves: 0m. No QC because volunteer accidentally rinsed out sulphuric acid vials. Wind picked up and temp increased throughout sampling. Lots of fish jumping and people fishing. Water is way clearer than last time. Only brought a 5m euphotic tubing accidentally so sampled to 5.0m instead of 7.6m. Microcystin ID: M200081. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow.

GPS: 49.4116302, -114.1026098. Wind: 3 km/hr S. Waves: 0.02m. Very calm in morning, warmed up by end of sampling. Foggy/smokey. Weeds in long arm of lake better than August but still had to move sites closer to main basin. Lots of fish jumping. Microcystin ID: M200080. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow.

GPS: 51.033407, -113.81367. Wind: 16 km/h NE. Waves: 0.15m. Late spring this year, ice off by May 1st, fish kill by May 15 (>200 fish according to volunteers). Different thick green algae bloom this year, very foamy. Lots of Suckers. Saw 2 dead fish. Had to re-calibrate depth because couldn't get 0.1m reading (saved as 0.6m on surveyor). Took profile a bit too far East because Kathy was adamant that was the deepest spot, howver we found 6.4m closer to West shore. Took beach grab samples at Anniversary Park and Cove Beach. Microcystin ID: M200099. Probe: MS5 41488. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.03361, -113.81444. Wind: 18 km/h NNW. Waves: 0.1m. Wind was quite high in the morning but calmed down by 11:00. Thick green algae from June is gone. GPS not working so used coordinates from phone compass. Microcystin ID: M200098. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.03367, -113.81474. Wind: 6 km/h E. Waves: 0.05m. Backswimmers in AIS haul but not Zoop haul. Not much algae in the water. Volunteer says weeds are the worst right now. Beaches have been closed for fecal bacteria. Depth on probe wouldn't calibrate properly first 3 times but seemed to work fine after. Microcystin ID: M200097. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow

GPS: 51.033547, -113.814878. Wind: 11 km/h S. Waves: 0.15m. Weeds on west side are much less prolific. Flowering rush by volunteer's dock. Beach was not busy at all. Used tape and weight for depth. Microcystin ID M200096. Tow Net.
very clear, see to bottom. Extra phyto & microsystin collected at 4m due to supersaturation in profile.
calm no wind, fishing boat out, pair of loons.
some very tiny ball algae.

Lots of Gleotrichia in watre column. Substrate sampler installed at end of dock.  Recent heavy rain in area overnight.
Very Windy. Had to re-anchor at profile depth 5m due to drift.  Definite color tinge to water from inflow streams.  Very sparse algae visible in column and zoo haul.
calm, lots of balls like algae
Winds picked up during profile. Had to relocate closer to buoy 2 times.

GPS: 53.46626, -117.79832. Wind: 19 km/hr SW. Waves:0.05 m. Large deep spot section, may have been off from last sampling date. Collected water at 7.5 m. with kemmerer. Metalimnetic bloom grab at 7.5 m (oxygen spike metalimnetic bloom). Preserved on September 28th from walkin cooler.

GPS: 54.26040 -110.74070. Wind: 15 km/hr W. Waves: 0.25m. Area/shorline is flooded. Paths and a bridge normally used to access bird watching tower was flooded. Wind began high, but died down. Very low human activity. Microcystin ID: M200129 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")
GPS: 54.2594 -110.7441. Wind: 10 km/hr W. Waves: 0. Extremly high density of blue-green algae at shoreline. Strong odor and build up at shore. Microcystin ID: M200126 Probe # 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 54.2594 -110.7475. Wind: 11 km/hr NW. Waves: 0.01m. Water levels are down since June/July. Less blue-green. Still particles and some clumping occuring. Microcystin ID: M200128 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 54.2590 -110.7468. Wind: 8 km/hr SW. Waves: 0. Very clear, not turbid. Blue-green algae particles throughout the water column. Some blue-green scums on shore, but no odor. Microcystin ID: M200127 Probe # 49593 TOW NET(8")

SampleComment: GPS: 53.95083 -114.34611. Wind: 6 km/hr E. Waves: 0.1m. Water levels are up from last year. Calm, but raining. Became more windy during final comp sites. Lots of cyanobacteria particles in water column. Small Pike was checking out the euphotic tubing during water haul. Microcystin ID: M200152. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET (8")

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.95083 -114.34611. Wind: 11 km/hr W. Waves: 0.35m. Lots of blue-green on South East point (balls/clumps). Blue-green through lake. Windy at the profile site, we drifted and had to move back into the profile site. Water was calm for the remainder of the sampling trip. Microcystin ID: M200153. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET (8")

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.95083 -114.34611. Wind: 8 km/hr W. Waves: 0.20m. Heavy winds and rainfall the night before. Floating weeds not as common this year. South eastern tip was higher in visable blue-green algae. Microcystin ID: M200154. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET (8")

Station: LAC LA NONNE, WHOLE LAKE COMPOSITE
SampleComment: GPS: 53.9475 -114.3477. Wind: 10 km/hr SW. Waves: 0.05m. Water levels down roughly 5". More blue-green in south basin. Blue-green streaks. Microcystin ID: M200151. Probe #: 49593 TOW NET (8")

GPS: 53.8377 -111.5819. Wind: 5 km/hr NW. Waves: 0. Water visability was very high. Lost disk portion of secchi disk. Not many boats on the water. Higher water levels than previous years. Very calm and warm day. Microcystin ID: M200164. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET(8")

GPS: 53.8377 -111.5819. Wind: 8 km/hr SSW. Waves: 0.25m. No signs of cyano on shore or milfoil near docks. Blue-green has increased, but not looking to have bloomed. Saved San205 under June sampling date. 1m calibration seemed off. central basin had some early signs of streaking (sites 4,5). Many developed properties in Northbay. Lots of large unnatural beaches. Water levels have consumed some beaches. Two county's control lake and limt development. Terry and Brian took us to old boat launch 150-200m from shoreline. Microcystin ID: M200165. Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")

GPS: 53.8377 -111.5819. Wind: 13 km/hr NE. Waves: 0.4m. Slight drift at profile site. Particles of blue-green, but overall not bad. Water levels going down slightly since last trip. Doing water hauls without foot valves. Ryan forgot it and was fired immediately. Microcystin ID: M200166. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET(8")

GPS: 53.8377 -111.5819. Wind: 8 km/hr S. Waves: 0.09m. Potentially off Redox (turned out to be normal). Water slightly down. Missing 0.1m 12.5m reading on surveyor ( added comment during data upload). Microcystin ID: M200167. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET(8")

GPS: 52.43107, -113.79845, Wind: 3 km/h NNW. Waves: 0. Water very clear, could see to bottom. Saw leeches, little crustaceans, grebes. Very calm in the morning. Couldn't sample the northern side (sites 8 &9) or southern side (sites 6& 7) because of thick macrophyte growth so squished comp sites in where it was deep enough. Euphotic depth > deepest point so wrote 2m on bottles and request forms. Microcystin ID: M200091. Probe: 60444. Net: Tow
GPS: 52.43107, -113.79845. Wind: 23 km/h WNW. Waves: 0.15m. Quite windy, more calm near south. Rained a bit. motor died so moved site 9 further south. Microcystin ID: M200090. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow

GPS: 52.43155, -113.79848. Wind: 5 km/h SW. Waves: 0.02m. Adjusted comp sites in South bay because too shallow/weedy. Volunteer also gave a wetland sample. Microcystin ID: M200089. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow
GPS: 52.43143, -113.79779. Wind: 10 km/h SSW. Waves: 0.05m. Loons are gone. Saw an eagle. Very weedy near rowing club. Microcystin ID: M200088. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow

GPS: 50.653591, -115.136922. Wind: 14 km/hr SE to NW. Waves: 0.3m. Water was clearer than last time and up a few feet. Coordinates wrong so adjusted after using google maps. pH probe readings were faulty, correct all values by -1.81. Microcystin ID: M200077. Probe:41488. Net: Tow
GPS: 50.65141, -115.13840. Wind: 4 km/hr W. Waves: 0. Super calm at start of profile. Ash on the surface of water, sort of hazy. Microcystin ID: M200078. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow

GPS: 50.65157, -115.13832. Wind: 20 km/hr SE. Waves: 0.15m. Zoop net hit bottom on first haul, rinsed and re-did haul. Very windy, drifted quite a bit downwind then tried to get back to 30m at profile site using engine. 100m cord did not work, so used 50m cord. Microcystin ID: M200076. Probe: 47482. Net:Tow

GPS: 53.48648, -114.30001. Wind: 3 km/h NNW. Waves: 0. Electric motor died half way so we rowed the rest of the way. SW arm on map is non-existent (marsh) so took one sample more in the main basin and eliminated 2 (see map). There is cattle on the West side. Lots of algae/macrophyte growth in between East and West basins and in SW arm. Microcystin ID: M200112. Probe: 60444. Net: Tow.

GPS: 53.4866, -114.2999. Wind: 6 km/h S. Waves: 0.02m. Did 2 horizontal mussel tows since water too shallow. Noticed hole in tube on tow net basket, duct taped it after profile site. Microcystin ID: M200111. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow.

GPS: 53.4866322, -114.299462. Wind: 10 km/h WSW. Waves: 0.03m. Tape and Weight showed bottom was about 6.9m but redox and conductivity measures etc. Indicate bottom was at 6.0m - maybe very soft bottom or depth calibrated wrong? Microcystin ID: M200110. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.486289, -114.299469. Wind: 8 km/h WNW. Waves: 0. Weeds still quite dense in  the south basin. Used tape and weight for depth during profile (probe was off ~0.25m). Microcystin ID: M200109. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.48889, -114.31169. Wind: 2 km/h S. Waves: 0. Map is outdated - max depth = 19m not 27 on map. Strong thermocline. Zoo net hit bottom so rinsed well and re-did haul. Microcystin ID: M200108. Probe: 60444. Net: Tow
GPS: 53.48914, -114.31385. Wind: 5km/h S. Waves: 0.05m. Water level is up since last time according to Al. Rained for about 10 mins. Microcystin ID: M200107. Probe: 41488. Net: Tow

GPS: 53.48907, -114.31309. Wind: 13 km/h WNW. Waves: 0.06m. Used Al Steinke's tin boat. Wind picked up at start of sampling but calmed by end of profile. Depth finder read 24m so didn't revert to 0.5m intervals at end of profile by the time I hit bottom at 22m. Microcystin ID: M200106. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow., Samples re-run by lab due to disagreement of QC. New results loaded. Original COA in DIVA.

GPS: 53.489035, -114.313562. Wind: 13 km/h NNW. Waves: 0.07m. Windier than East basin. Fisherman said he's caught lots of fish today. Used tape and weight for depth because probe was off. Microcystin ID:M200105. Probe: 47482. Net: Tow.  Odour observation not recorded in the field.

GPS: 54.52165 -110.50024. Wind: 10 km/hr E. Waves: 0.3m. Very sunny and busy. Plenty of wake boats and beach swimmers. Joined by Ron's Neighbour. Microcystin ID: M200163 Probe #: 49593 TOW NET(8")
GPS: 54.52165 -110.50024. Wind: 10 km/hr SE. Waves: 0.05m. Calm water. Not much Zooplankton in the haul, compared to previous zoo hauls. Microcystin ID: M200162. Probe #: 49593. TOW NET(8")
